WEBVTT

00:26.111 --> 00:27.904
(MUSIC PLAYING)

00:32.784 --> 00:34.869
<i>NARRATOR: Following months
of high rainfall,</i>

00:34.953 --> 00:38.790
<i>the river Seine begins to rise
more rapidly than normal.</i>

00:38.873 --> 00:40.625
<i>Over the course of the last week,</i>

00:40.709 --> 00:43.420
<i>thousands of Parisians living nearby the river</i>

00:43.503 --> 00:45.422
<i>have already evacuated.</i>

00:45.755 --> 00:47.882
<i>To continue moving throughout the city,</i>

00:47.966 --> 00:50.427
<i>residents travel by boat or across</i>

00:50.510 --> 00:54.681
<i>a series of wooden walkways
built by Parisians themselves.</i>

00:54.764 --> 00:58.560
<i>The water reaches a height
of 20 feet above the normal.</i>

00:58.810 --> 01:01.146
<i>The Eiffel Tower has wet feet.</i>

01:01.229 --> 01:06.109
<i>And it's only on the Montmartre hill
that people can stay a little dry.</i>

01:15.869 --> 01:17.662
(AUDIENCE MURMURING)

01:34.679 --> 01:35.722
(LAUGHING)

01:37.849 --> 01:39.517
Emile, hey! Over here!

01:40.894 --> 01:42.020
(SIGHS)

01:44.606 --> 01:47.108
- Let me take that.
-(GIGGLES) Thanks.

01:48.818 --> 01:51.154
You know, Emile, I only have one regret.

01:51.237 --> 01:52.947
You do? What?

01:53.448 --> 01:55.950
That it took you two years
to ask me for a date.

01:56.242 --> 01:58.119
I... I was scared you'd say no.

01:58.203 --> 02:00.830
Oh, Emile. l wish I had known.

02:01.581 --> 02:03.082
All that time wasted.

02:03.541 --> 02:05.376
Maud, my darling.
Don't let your mind dwell on that.

02:06.503 --> 02:08.545
The past is past. The future is ours.

02:08.713 --> 02:11.049
Nothing. Nothing can come between us now.

02:11.424 --> 02:12.509
(SCREAMS)

02:13.092 --> 02:14.469
-(ROARS)
-(BOTH SCREAM)

02:15.970 --> 02:17.013
Emile!

02:17.096 --> 02:18.306
(GASPS)

02:19.265 --> 02:20.350
(GRUNTS)

02:21.392 --> 02:22.644
(SCREAMING)

02:23.394 --> 02:26.773
(CHUCKLES) It's show time! What do you got?

02:27.398 --> 02:30.735
To the left! Yes, parry! To the right!

02:30.860 --> 02:32.362
- Whoa!
-(SCREAMS)

02:32.570 --> 02:33.738
It's a dragon!

02:33.822 --> 02:35.615
What on earth is a dragon doing in France?

02:35.824 --> 02:37.492
What on earth is a dragon doing on earth?

02:37.700 --> 02:38.743
(SCREAMS)

02:38.827 --> 02:39.911
(ROARS)

02:40.912 --> 02:42.497
(AUDIENCE GROANS)

02:43.373 --> 02:44.457
(GASPS)

02:45.834 --> 02:46.876
Oh, no!

02:47.752 --> 02:49.045
(AUDIENCE JEERING)

02:53.049 --> 02:55.093
Okay, come on! Here it is!

02:57.720 --> 02:59.264
(SCATTERED APPLAUSE)

03:02.934 --> 03:04.060
Whew.

03:15.321 --> 03:17.365
- Come on.
-(EXCLAIMS)

03:18.741 --> 03:19.951
(GRUNTS)

03:21.202 --> 03:22.370
(SIGHS)

03:22.453 --> 03:23.538
Hmm.

03:29.794 --> 03:31.462
(HUMMING)

03:35.258 --> 03:36.885
-(SIGHS)
-(BACKFIRING)

03:37.051 --> 03:38.136
(GASPS)

03:38.469 --> 03:39.596
(CLANGING)

03:39.679 --> 03:41.139
Hey. (COUGHS)

03:41.973 --> 03:43.308
-(GASPS)
- Hello, Raoul.

03:43.433 --> 03:46.102
Well, hello, Maud.
Look at you. Petite as always.

03:46.185 --> 03:47.729
That's a lovely dress. What is that?

03:47.812 --> 03:49.147
- Kind of an eggplant?
- Oh, thank you.

03:49.230 --> 03:50.857
Um, I think it's more of a purple.

03:50.940 --> 03:51.983
More of an eggplant I think.

03:52.066 --> 03:53.359
Is Emile in? I have something for him.

03:53.443 --> 03:55.653
No, I guess it is kind of an eggplant.

03:55.778 --> 03:56.905
(CLEARS THROAT)

03:56.988 --> 03:58.781
- Oh. The new Méliés film!
- Mmm-hmm.

03:58.865 --> 04:00.783
He'll be so excited, it's his idol.

04:00.867 --> 04:01.993
- Hey, Emile!
- Oh!

04:02.285 --> 04:03.828
- Hey, Raoul!
- Catch this!

04:04.120 --> 04:05.204
(GRUNTS)

04:05.496 --> 04:06.581
(EXCLAIMS)

04:07.665 --> 04:10.043
Oh! Oh, that's embarrassing.

04:10.126 --> 04:11.169
(GIGGLES)

04:11.252 --> 04:12.462
'Hey, You!
"Oh!

04:12.545 --> 04:13.588
Come on, come on. Quick.

04:13.671 --> 04:15.173
Okay, not looking.

04:16.382 --> 04:18.426
- I can't see anything now.
- Come on, come on!

04:19.636 --> 04:20.762
Going somewhere, Emile?

04:20.845 --> 04:22.805
I have to go to Barbés to buy a new belt.

04:22.889 --> 04:23.932
Obviously.

04:24.015 --> 04:27.018
Oh, no, no. A belt for my projector.

04:27.477 --> 04:30.188
(CHUCKLES) Since when do you put
pants on your projector?

04:30.355 --> 04:31.522
(LAUGHS)

04:31.689 --> 04:35.193
- Pants on my projector?
- Yeah, because uh... Never mind.

04:35.360 --> 04:36.861
Do you need a lift? It's on my route.

04:36.945 --> 04:38.571
Catherine is right...

04:38.696 --> 04:40.406
Oh! Catherine!

04:40.490 --> 04:42.116
(YELLS) Come on! Could you stop the...

04:42.200 --> 04:43.201
-(CLATTERING)
-(WOMAN GASPS)

04:43.284 --> 04:44.327
Sorry! Come here!

04:44.410 --> 04:46.120
- Come on, bad truck! Come back.
-(CLEARS THROAT)

04:46.204 --> 04:49.916
(STAMMERS) So, I'll see you later
at the screening?

04:50.541 --> 04:52.877
Yes. Uh, yes, you will.

04:55.463 --> 04:57.548
(STAMMERING) You know, Maud,

04:58.132 --> 04:59.717
I was wondering if...

05:00.510 --> 05:01.928
If you don't mind...

05:02.971 --> 05:06.683
- Uh, maybe... Maybe you would...
- Yes! Of course I would.

05:07.225 --> 05:08.476
You would?

05:08.559 --> 05:11.688
Yes, I would gladly take that reel
back to your room, no problem.

05:11.896 --> 05:13.564
Ah, yes, yes... That!

05:14.691 --> 05:16.943
Well, yes, of course... I mean, thank you.

05:17.026 --> 05:19.028
Uh, here. Thank you, Maud.

05:19.862 --> 05:21.698
Um, anything else, Emile?

05:22.407 --> 05:23.908
Yes. Uh...

05:24.659 --> 05:28.830
(STAMMERING) Well, I thought perhaps
after the screening...

05:28.913 --> 05:31.416
Emile, buddy! Let's shake a leg.
I'm on a schedule here.

05:31.499 --> 05:34.293
You'll have plenty of time
to woo Maud when you're back.

05:35.878 --> 05:36.921
(GIGGLES)

05:37.880 --> 05:38.923
Bye!

05:40.133 --> 05:42.010
(CHURCH BELLS TOLLING)

05:46.431 --> 05:48.516
EMILE: Well, thank you very much, Raoul!

05:48.599 --> 05:50.351
Well, you're very welcome, Emile.

05:50.810 --> 05:51.936
Uh, for what?

05:52.395 --> 05:54.147
I was talking to her and you ruined it!

05:54.230 --> 05:56.774
You little devil, you!
Let me pinch those cheeks.

05:57.150 --> 05:59.152
You finally decided to ask her out, didn't you?

05:59.235 --> 06:01.154
Well, no, it's so complicated.

06:01.279 --> 06:03.990
What's so complicated?
You ask her out, she swoons.

06:04.073 --> 06:07.160
She says yes, you swoon back.
Deal sealed. You're on a date.

06:07.285 --> 06:09.120
EMILE: It's not that simple.

06:09.787 --> 06:10.872
Every time I see her,

06:10.955 --> 06:13.249
my tongue kind of gets glued
to the top of my mouth.

06:13.750 --> 06:15.877
Which is why you write her a letter.

06:16.127 --> 06:18.004
The only thing you have to glue then
is an envelope. (GIGGLES)

06:18.546 --> 06:19.922
A letter.

06:20.048 --> 06:21.090
That's not a bad idea!

06:21.174 --> 06:23.134
Of course that's not a bad idea.
It's a great idea. I had it!

06:23.259 --> 06:24.260
I'll help you if you want.

06:24.343 --> 06:25.720
I got a way with words as you know.

06:25.803 --> 06:26.888
EMILE: (STUTTERING) Well... I do know.

06:26.971 --> 06:29.057
But do you know much about love, Raoul?

06:29.140 --> 06:30.892
Do I... (LAUGHS)

06:31.601 --> 06:34.520
Oh, you are adorable. Do I know about love?

06:34.937 --> 06:36.814
Do you have any idea
what they say around Paris?

06:36.898 --> 06:41.402
When Raoul is on the prowl,
the kitty cats all meow!

06:42.278 --> 06:45.782
- EMILE: Oh. That does rhyme.
- It better than rhymes, my friend.

06:48.493 --> 06:49.577
Hello, Madame Omelette!

06:49.660 --> 06:51.079
Hope you're not feeling too scrambled today

06:51.162 --> 06:52.830
and you're feeling nice and over-easy.

06:52.914 --> 06:53.956
(CHUCKLES)

06:54.040 --> 06:55.291
Where... Where are my eggs?

06:55.666 --> 06:57.126
It's not that I don't trust you, Raoul,

06:57.210 --> 06:59.420
but the way you drive,
I figured it's safer to deliver the eggs

06:59.504 --> 07:00.963
-with a little padding.
-(CLUCKING)

07:01.047 --> 07:02.131
(CHUCKLING)

07:02.632 --> 07:03.883
(GROANS) Great!

07:05.093 --> 07:06.219
(SNEEZING)

07:08.971 --> 07:11.224
- Raoul, are you okay?
- No I'm fine, it's just...

07:11.307 --> 07:13.309
(SNEEZES VIOLENTLY) Allergies!

07:13.392 --> 07:14.685
(CONTINUES SNEEZING)

07:15.186 --> 07:16.270
MAN: Hey!

07:17.355 --> 07:19.023
- Moron!
- RAOUL: Sorry, honey!

07:19.107 --> 07:21.317
EMILE: You drive very fast!

07:21.400 --> 07:22.485
I know!

07:22.568 --> 07:25.863
Ever since Catherine runs on
sunflower oil, she really flies.

07:27.949 --> 07:31.494
Uh, speaking of flies...
Your coat. It's very itchy!

07:31.953 --> 07:33.287
It feels like straw.

07:33.830 --> 07:36.582
Straw? Are you kidding? What I paid for this?

07:36.666 --> 07:38.209
(LAUGHS) Oh, Emile.

07:38.292 --> 07:41.379
This is genuine 100%... (SNEEZES)

07:41.462 --> 07:42.588
...rare!

07:42.672 --> 07:46.592
The flood of the century!
Commissioner's popularity sinks as...

07:46.676 --> 07:48.344
- As fast as the water rises!
- Uh, Raoul!

07:48.427 --> 07:49.637
(HORN HONKING)

07:49.720 --> 07:51.139
Oh! (SCREAMS)

07:51.222 --> 07:52.765
-(BOTH SCREAMING)
-(TYRES SCREECHING)

07:55.268 --> 07:56.352
Whoa!

07:58.563 --> 07:59.605
(CLUCKING)

07:59.689 --> 08:00.898
(BOTH SCREAMING)

08:01.566 --> 08:02.692
(TYRES SCREECHING)

08:04.944 --> 08:05.987
Oh.

08:10.867 --> 08:11.909
Oh, no.

08:12.368 --> 08:13.619
(SNEEZING VIOLENTLY)

08:17.999 --> 08:20.334
RAOUL: (SHOUTING) <i>I</i> hate birds!

08:27.550 --> 08:30.428
- EMILE: Thank you, Raoul!
- Don't mention it, big man!

08:30.511 --> 08:32.013
See you later!

08:32.929 --> 08:34.849
Hey! Watch where you're going!

08:34.932 --> 08:36.100
(CHUCKLING)

08:37.977 --> 08:40.104
Here. A brand new second-hand belt.

08:40.770 --> 08:42.940
- Anything else?
- Uh, maybe.

08:43.024 --> 08:45.109
Mmm-hmm. She's a beauty, isn't she?

08:46.068 --> 08:47.612
Oh, yes!

08:48.362 --> 08:49.864
(WHISTLING)

08:54.452 --> 08:56.287
- What's that?
- What is that?

08:56.454 --> 08:57.914
That is the future!

08:58.080 --> 09:00.124
No, that! Is it straw?

09:00.208 --> 09:02.543
No. Okay. Now, back to the future.

09:02.627 --> 09:05.046
You see? No more blisters,
no more dirty clothes,

09:05.129 --> 09:06.214
no more aches and pains.

09:06.297 --> 09:08.966
All comfort, no effort! That's the future.

09:09.050 --> 09:11.135
- Okay. But what does it do?
- What does it do?

09:11.344 --> 09:12.470
It does...

09:13.638 --> 09:14.722
(EXCLAIMS)

09:15.139 --> 09:16.224
(SPUTTERING)

09:17.225 --> 09:18.893
(BOTH CHUCKLING EMBARRASSEDLY)

09:19.477 --> 09:20.519
(CLEARS THROAT) Well...

09:20.895 --> 09:22.772
- Bye-bye now! Thank you.
- Thank you.

09:23.189 --> 09:24.232
Uh, bye!

09:24.440 --> 09:26.234
(SIGHS) My camera.

09:26.525 --> 09:28.694
Oh, look at that!

09:29.237 --> 09:30.321
(LAUGHS)

09:31.030 --> 09:32.823
This is beautiful.

09:32.907 --> 09:35.284
That's... That's my camera.

09:35.910 --> 09:36.994
Wait! He's running away.

09:37.245 --> 09:39.163
Thief! (PANTING) Thief!

09:42.041 --> 09:43.626
Okay? Well, okay. Oh, right, right, right.

09:43.834 --> 09:45.336
- My camera!
- MAN: Hey, stop, thief!

09:47.964 --> 09:49.006
(GROANS)

09:50.841 --> 09:52.677
Oh, no. It's not supposed to do that.

09:53.844 --> 09:55.513
Huh? That's fantastic!

09:56.514 --> 09:57.682
(GRUNTING)

09:58.724 --> 10:00.309
It worked great yesterday!

10:00.393 --> 10:01.519
(BLOWING)

10:01.602 --> 10:02.812
(BLARING LOUDLY)

10:05.147 --> 10:07.358
Okay. Maybe if I just press...

10:07.817 --> 10:09.402
-(GASPS)
- Oh. Hey!

10:10.319 --> 10:12.363
One. Two.

10:13.781 --> 10:14.824
And it's supposed to do that?

10:14.907 --> 10:16.534
Raoul! Thank you. Thank you so much!

10:17.285 --> 10:18.369
You saved my life!

10:18.536 --> 10:20.621
- Uh, I did?
- Yes. Look.

10:25.626 --> 10:27.545
And three. And I meant to do that!

10:28.045 --> 10:30.214
Now, we are all nice and warmed up,
let's deliver those babies.

10:31.007 --> 10:32.633
(STAMMERING) Uh, I don't know if I can.

10:32.717 --> 10:33.801
It's just that I don't want to be late.

10:34.218 --> 10:35.720
Don't worry. We're gonna get there in a flash.

10:47.189 --> 10:48.482
(RAOUL WHISTLING)

10:52.570 --> 10:53.571
Wow!

10:54.363 --> 10:56.324
RAOUL: You're gonna love the professor.
He's a real character.

10:56.407 --> 10:59.160
Way ahead of his time.
A real visionary. A little like myself.

10:59.869 --> 11:01.537
Too bad he never lets me see his work.

11:01.662 --> 11:02.872
Maybe he's shy?

11:02.955 --> 11:05.041
Yes, maybe. Professor!

11:06.751 --> 11:08.252
- Oh, apparently very shy!
- Hmm.

11:08.919 --> 11:09.962
Okay, what have we got?

11:10.046 --> 11:11.714
"Dear Raoul, I am in New York
for a conference.

11:11.797 --> 11:12.882
"Just leave the peat outside.

11:12.965 --> 11:14.967
"In my absence, Charles will take care of it."

11:15.051 --> 11:16.052
- Hmm.
- Who's Charles?

11:16.135 --> 11:17.219
(CHUCKLES)

11:18.888 --> 11:20.514
- RAOUL: Charles, come on.
-(SNIFFING)

11:22.892 --> 11:23.934
Oh!

11:25.269 --> 11:27.480
Oh! "Charles, Assistant Botanist."

11:28.064 --> 11:29.231
Hello, Charles.

11:29.315 --> 11:31.859
Now, let's get those precious bags inside.

11:31.942 --> 11:33.361
We wouldn't want them to get wet.
Right, Charles?

11:33.444 --> 11:34.779
-(SCREECHING)
- What? Okay.

11:35.279 --> 11:37.406
"Well, now that you're inside,
just leave the peat at the door.

11:37.490 --> 11:39.533
"Whatever you do, don't..." (GRUNTS)
"...touch anything."

11:39.617 --> 11:40.951
"Thank you. Good day."

11:41.285 --> 11:42.495
Okay. Okay, I get it.

11:44.121 --> 11:45.581
The professor seems to know you pretty well!

11:45.748 --> 11:46.749
Yeah. Yeah.

11:47.124 --> 11:48.376
(WHISTLING)

11:49.043 --> 11:50.169
EMILE: WOW!

11:52.797 --> 11:54.632
- Beautiful.
-(GRUNTING)

11:55.383 --> 11:58.302
Another job well done.
For peat's sake! Right?

11:59.095 --> 12:01.597
(LAUGHS) 'Cause it's peat!
Get it? Do you get it?

12:01.680 --> 12:02.681
Pete's sake?

12:03.182 --> 12:04.225
You're a monkey.

12:08.145 --> 12:09.730
All right! Ready for a quick tour?

12:09.814 --> 12:11.774
But the monkey said
we weren't supposed to...

12:12.024 --> 12:13.734
The monkey said, come on! You could film it!

12:13.818 --> 12:16.070
Imagine, Your own jungle movie!
I play the brave explorer.

12:16.153 --> 12:17.780
- What do you think?
- You think I could?

12:18.239 --> 12:20.408
(LAUGHS) You are... Yeah, of course!

12:20.491 --> 12:21.575
(WHISPERS) Let's get to it!

12:21.992 --> 12:24.078
Right. (CLEARS THROAT) We'll call him...

12:24.328 --> 12:25.704
Let's call him Jeff,

12:25.996 --> 12:27.331
with my companion Charlie

12:27.415 --> 12:31.293
and we're going to save the damsel
from the dark regions of the jungle.

12:31.669 --> 12:33.254
-(SCREECHING)
- Oh, my... Look at that monster!

12:34.380 --> 12:35.965
EMILE: What kind of tree is that?

12:36.674 --> 12:40.678
Well, that, Emile,
it's an Extremus Gigantis Circus uh...

12:40.886 --> 12:42.012
Asparagus.

12:44.390 --> 12:46.350
-(HOOTING)
- Actually, it's a sequoia.

12:47.184 --> 12:49.145
A sequoia? Yes. Call it a sequoia.

12:49.228 --> 12:50.896
If you prefer the generic name.

12:51.021 --> 12:54.233
Oh, my... Look at that! it's the professor's lab!

12:56.694 --> 12:59.447
Emile! Emile! Come and get a shot of me!

13:00.948 --> 13:03.325
(LAUGHING ECSTATICALLY)

13:04.326 --> 13:06.036
Okay! What do we got? "Do not use."

13:06.120 --> 13:07.371
All right. Let's see what it does.

13:07.455 --> 13:09.540
- Are you filming?
- Yes, but it says do not use...

13:09.623 --> 13:11.041
No. (MUMBLING INDISTINCTLY)

13:12.251 --> 13:13.294
Oh!

13:13.377 --> 13:14.420
(COUGHING)

13:18.382 --> 13:21.260
(SIGHS) Huh? Right. Okay, next.

13:21.927 --> 13:23.471
How about this one? "Atomise-a-tune."

13:23.554 --> 13:25.389
Atomise-a-tune. Good name!

13:25.639 --> 13:27.808
"Blah blah blah...
For a more melodious voice."

13:27.892 --> 13:29.185
(SCREECHING)

13:34.648 --> 13:37.067
(SINGING WITH OPERATIC VOICE)

13:37.985 --> 13:39.904
(LAUGHING) That's incredible!

13:40.237 --> 13:43.282
That's amazing!
Charles, you have a lovely singing voice.

13:43.574 --> 13:45.576
All right let's try this one.
"Super-Fertilizer." Hmm.

13:45.659 --> 13:46.744
"Unstable."

13:46.994 --> 13:49.288
Okay. Now all I need now is a little seed.

13:50.164 --> 13:53.083
From this jar, here.
A tiny drop, or two. And then we wait.

13:54.710 --> 13:56.629
And we continue to wait.

13:58.422 --> 13:59.548
And we wait.

13:59.924 --> 14:01.634
This one's a... This one's a dud.

14:01.926 --> 14:04.345
- Maybe you need to water it.
- Good idea, Emile.

14:04.678 --> 14:05.763
(HUMMING)

14:11.810 --> 14:13.562
Very disappointing, Professor.

14:13.979 --> 14:15.147
Okay. Next!

14:15.606 --> 14:19.109
RAOUL: Let's see if the old geezer invented
anything that actually works?

14:21.195 --> 14:22.238
(GASPS)

14:22.321 --> 14:23.822
-(SCREAMS)
- EMILE: Whoa!

14:24.657 --> 14:25.741
Wow!

14:27.284 --> 14:28.369
(WHISPERS) Did you get that?

14:28.953 --> 14:31.121
- I did! All of it!
-(LAUGHING)

14:31.455 --> 14:34.124
God! A sunflower that big
must produce tons of oil.

14:34.208 --> 14:36.835
This could cut Catherine's fuel budget by 10.

14:37.545 --> 14:39.630
Emile, this must be my lucky day!

14:39.797 --> 14:40.798
(WHIMPERS)

14:41.006 --> 14:42.007
(CREAKING)

14:42.466 --> 14:43.968
- Emile!
-(CHARLES SCREECHING)

14:46.971 --> 14:48.180
(GRUNTS)

14:59.149 --> 15:00.234
(EXPLOSION)

15:07.491 --> 15:08.701
(COUGHING)

15:23.048 --> 15:24.592
Huh? What?

15:27.219 --> 15:28.262
(EXCLAIMS)

15:29.013 --> 15:30.097
(GASPS)

15:32.850 --> 15:33.934
(SCREAMING)

15:44.111 --> 15:45.446
(GROANING)

15:47.656 --> 15:49.199
Raoul? Raoul?

15:49.867 --> 15:51.493
Raoul! Raoul, are you okay?

15:51.577 --> 15:53.704
(SHUDDERING)

15:54.163 --> 15:56.415
Yeah. I think... I think the coat saved my life.

15:56.498 --> 15:59.001
Emile? Emile! I'm okay! I'm okay.

15:59.251 --> 16:01.128
Oh. Good. Good.

16:01.211 --> 16:03.631
(GASPS) Charles! Where is Charles?

16:04.298 --> 16:05.549
Charles?

16:06.592 --> 16:07.718
"Look up."

16:08.218 --> 16:09.720
Huh? Oh!

16:09.928 --> 16:11.930
-(LAUGHS) Hey, Charles!
-(HOOTING)

16:12.556 --> 16:14.725
Right, good, Charles is fine.
You're fine. I'm fine.

16:14.808 --> 16:16.018
The plants are fine. Everything's fine.

16:16.101 --> 16:17.311
(SHATTERING)

16:17.394 --> 16:20.189
There. So, I think we'll be going now.
Good night.

16:20.356 --> 16:21.607
It's been a pleasure.

16:24.526 --> 16:26.153
Raoul. Raoul?

16:26.487 --> 16:28.906
You didn't see something
strange in there, did you?

16:29.490 --> 16:31.659
You mean besides a singing monkey,

16:31.742 --> 16:34.995
a 50 foot sunflower
and vials of potions that almost killed us?

16:35.079 --> 16:36.955
No. You see anything strange?

16:37.039 --> 16:39.375
(STAMMERING) You mean you didn't see
a seven foot creature

16:39.708 --> 16:42.670
with big red bug eyes, four arms,
and spikes all over his body?

16:42.753 --> 16:44.129
(CHUCKLING)

16:44.421 --> 16:47.758
Emile. I think somebody has been
watching too many movies.

16:48.092 --> 16:49.259
- You think?
- Yes, my friend.

16:49.343 --> 16:50.594
(SNEEZES)

16:53.639 --> 16:55.140
(HORN BLARING)

17:21.458 --> 17:22.710
(MUSIC PLAYING ON PHONOGRAPH)

17:23.794 --> 17:25.128
(SINGING ALONG)

17:26.588 --> 17:27.964
(SCREAMING)

17:30.217 --> 17:31.552
(MAN SCREAMING)

17:34.972 --> 17:36.432
(WOMAN SCREAMING)

17:52.072 --> 17:53.949
MAN: With all this flooding,
what a dreadful winter...

17:54.032 --> 17:56.493
- Whoops!
- CARLOTTA: Very harsh winter, yes.

17:56.827 --> 17:58.203
- But I don't complain.
- Naturally.

17:58.287 --> 17:59.747
- We're lucky.
- Yes, we are.

17:59.830 --> 18:03.083
Uh, say, Madame Carlotta,
have you told Lucille about my songs yet?

18:03.167 --> 18:04.960
-(WHISPERS) Go on!
- Oh, okay.

18:05.836 --> 18:08.255
- Water goes where water goes.
- Mmm-hmm?

18:08.338 --> 18:10.674
Who do they think I am? Moses?

18:10.758 --> 18:12.342
Am I supposed to make miracles?

18:12.426 --> 18:15.053
Uh, no, but perhaps some boats,

18:15.137 --> 18:18.474
more walkways, shelters for
the poor, blankets...

18:18.557 --> 18:22.102
Forget blankets.
What's needed here is diversion.

18:22.186 --> 18:24.730
Oh, yes, perfect. We can divert the water.

18:24.813 --> 18:28.233
- Not water, Paté. Their minds.
- Oh.

18:28.317 --> 18:32.988
We need to get their minds out of the wet
and onto something big.

18:33.071 --> 18:35.657
Something that will wash this headline away

18:35.741 --> 18:39.995
and replace it with something
that will grab their imagination.

18:40.078 --> 18:41.497
Uh... Like What?

18:41.997 --> 18:45.125
I don't know.
Something that will have some pizzazz.

18:45.292 --> 18:46.627
Something that will pop!

18:47.252 --> 18:48.378
ALBERT: Whoa!

18:49.546 --> 18:50.631
Give me that!

18:50.964 --> 18:51.965
- What?
- Go!

18:52.049 --> 18:53.133
Not my fault!

18:53.217 --> 18:54.468
-(WHISPERS) Now!
- Whatever!

18:54.551 --> 18:57.471
Commissioner Maynott, Captain Paté,
I trust everything is to your liking?

18:57.554 --> 18:59.556
Oh, yes, my dear Carlotta, yes.

18:59.640 --> 19:01.183
Yes, of course it is, isn't it?

19:01.266 --> 19:03.769
- One step from perfection.
- One step from... Oh!

19:03.852 --> 19:05.229
All that is needed now is

19:05.938 --> 19:08.690
for your angel of a niece

19:08.774 --> 19:10.400
to accept my invitation.

19:10.567 --> 19:11.568
(LAUGHS)

19:11.735 --> 19:14.279
- With my compliments.
- Oh, Commissioner, what an honour!

19:14.363 --> 19:16.198
Oh, I'm sure she will be delighted.

19:16.281 --> 19:17.533
(LAUGHS)

19:18.116 --> 19:19.117
Oh, speak of the devil.

19:19.201 --> 19:20.285
-(AUDIENCE APPLAUDING)
- Ah!

19:20.369 --> 19:21.745
(PIANO PLAYING)

19:36.468 --> 19:38.345
<i># She is resplendent</i>

19:38.428 --> 19:40.097
# <i>So confident</i>

19:40.180 --> 19:43.267
<i># La Seine, La, Seine, La Seine</i>

19:44.768 --> 19:48.105
<i># I realise I'm hypnotised</i>

19:48.564 --> 19:51.775
<i># La Seine, La Seine, La Seine</i>

19:53.110 --> 19:56.446
<i># I hear the moon singing a tune</i>

19:57.072 --> 20:01.368
<i># "La Seine, La Seine, La Seine"</i>

20:01.785 --> 20:05.122
<i># Is she divine?
Is it the wine?</i>

20:05.706 --> 20:09.459
<i># La Seine, La Seine, La Seine</i>

20:09.585 --> 20:11.587
<i># I don't know, don't know</i>

20:11.837 --> 20:15.424
<i># So don't ask me why
that's how we are</i>

20:15.757 --> 20:17.259
# La Seine and <i>I</i>

20:18.218 --> 20:20.304
<i># I don't know, don't know</i>

20:20.387 --> 20:24.516
<i># So don't ask me why
that's how we are</i>

20:24.600 --> 20:26.310
# La Seine and <i>I</i>

20:28.854 --> 20:31.148
<i># I don't know, don't know</i>

20:31.231 --> 20:34.860
<i># So don't ask me why
that's how we are</i>

20:35.277 --> 20:36.987
# La Seine and <i>I</i>

20:37.321 --> 20:39.239
<i># That's how we are</i>

20:39.364 --> 20:41.325
# La Seine and <i>I</i> #

20:41.450 --> 20:42.868
(AUDIENCE APPLAUDING)

20:58.050 --> 20:59.134
Not interested.

20:59.217 --> 21:01.345
Everybody needs somebody. Even you!

21:01.553 --> 21:02.679
You look at the Commissioner.

21:02.763 --> 21:04.765
He's successful, he's a national figure.

21:04.848 --> 21:07.267
- He's pompous.
- He has a medal of honour!

21:07.351 --> 21:09.728
- He's boring.
- People respect him.

21:10.187 --> 21:12.606
He's got nice hair. Oh, I love his hair.

21:12.856 --> 21:14.358
He smells good, doesn't he?

21:14.483 --> 21:16.443
- He's attractive...
-(SIGHS) He's not my type!

21:16.777 --> 21:19.488
Not your type? Okay, maybe not yet.

21:19.863 --> 21:22.950
But you meet him,
you're nice, and he becomes your type.

21:23.033 --> 21:25.285
Perhaps you smile
that wonderful smile of yours.

21:25.369 --> 21:26.662
- And who knows?
-(SIGHS)

21:26.745 --> 21:28.664
Come on, let me see it.

21:28.872 --> 21:30.707
Ah, perfect! (LAUGHS)

21:35.045 --> 21:36.254
(SIGHS)

21:39.091 --> 21:41.843
- What a singer!
-(CHUCKLES) Mmm, and what a woman!

21:42.010 --> 21:43.345
What do you mean, "What a woman"?

21:43.428 --> 21:45.847
I'm wondering. Would you be jealous?

21:45.973 --> 21:47.391
- Oh, dear!
- What?

21:49.977 --> 21:52.229
(LAUGHS) I'll take care of that.

21:55.941 --> 21:57.025
There.

22:02.739 --> 22:03.782
(EXCLAIMS)

22:03.865 --> 22:06.284
- What's wrong?
- Something touched me!

22:06.493 --> 22:10.789
Oh! Don't worry, dear.
It won't attack a larger animal.

22:10.872 --> 22:12.582
-(HISSING)
-(CAT YOWLING)

22:12.708 --> 22:14.292
-(SCREAMS)
- What?

22:16.253 --> 22:17.337
(SCREAMS)

22:17.587 --> 22:20.007
Oh, God, no! No! Let me go!

22:20.090 --> 22:21.508
(WHIMPERING)

22:22.092 --> 22:24.302
- Go! Run!
-(SCREAMING)

22:24.386 --> 22:25.429
Run!

22:26.388 --> 22:27.389
(GROWLING)

22:29.224 --> 22:31.560
Oh, horrible. Seven feet tall,

22:32.728 --> 22:34.396
razor-sharp teeth.

22:35.022 --> 22:36.106
Horrible.

22:36.273 --> 22:38.942
- Yeah, of course. Sign here.
- Oh.

22:40.360 --> 22:41.820
How's it going with that sketch?

22:42.279 --> 22:43.572
(SIGHS)

22:43.864 --> 22:45.949
- Huh? Wait. Uh...
- He's getting good, huh?

22:52.956 --> 22:54.291
Let's see here.

22:54.499 --> 22:57.586
What could rhyme with "great destiny"?

22:58.628 --> 23:01.006
(CHUCKLES) Ah, yes, <i>I</i> know! "Me!"

23:01.131 --> 23:02.716
-(KNOCK ON DOOR)
- Come in!

23:04.259 --> 23:05.260
Paté.

23:06.011 --> 23:08.013
What in the world are you wearing?

23:08.138 --> 23:11.308
It's all part of the new fitness campaign
for elite officers.

23:11.391 --> 23:13.810
I have agreed to lead
the Rapid Response Bicycle Unit.

23:14.519 --> 23:16.396
Brilliant. Anything new?

23:17.439 --> 23:19.733
Well, it's just a theory but...

23:21.818 --> 23:24.362
Here is where the store window was smashed.

23:24.446 --> 23:25.489
Yes.

23:25.572 --> 23:27.824
- Here is where the children were traumatized.
- Okay.

23:27.908 --> 23:31.787
Here is where the horse was spooked
and stampeded through the lingerie shop.

23:31.870 --> 23:34.581
- See what I'm getting at?
- Uh... Actually no.

23:34.998 --> 23:37.125
There is a pattern, a logical progression,

23:37.209 --> 23:40.087
leading all the way to here.

23:40.253 --> 23:41.254
MAYNOTT: And?

23:41.463 --> 23:45.300
Well, I would like permission to do
a more thorough investigation,

23:45.383 --> 23:48.804
- Sir.
- Yes, of course, investigate away.

23:49.346 --> 23:52.474
Let the public see that we are men of action.

23:52.849 --> 23:55.102
- Thank you, sir. Thank you.
- Yeah. Hmm.

23:55.477 --> 23:57.562
But don't be too quick
at solving the case, Paté.

23:58.146 --> 24:00.065
But, sir, I should think the quicker the better.

24:00.148 --> 24:01.775
We are on the verge of a catastrophe.

24:01.858 --> 24:06.446
Where you see catastrophe, I see opportunity.

24:06.905 --> 24:08.740
You see, my dear Captain,

24:08.824 --> 24:12.160
when people are frightened
they need protection.

24:12.244 --> 24:14.538
They need someone that they can turn to,

24:15.163 --> 24:16.706
someone to believe in,

24:17.332 --> 24:18.542
a saviour,

24:19.084 --> 24:20.377
a hero.

24:20.460 --> 24:22.587
In other words, they need

24:23.964 --> 24:25.006
me!

24:30.679 --> 24:32.264
CARLOTTA: And say hello for me.
LUCILLE: Sure.

24:32.347 --> 24:33.682
CARLOTTA: No, don't.
You don't have to. No, no.

24:33.765 --> 24:35.225
I mean, well, if he mentions me.

24:35.308 --> 24:36.643
- LUCILLE: Okay!
- Oh, let me see...

24:36.726 --> 24:38.145
Darling, wait. Stop. Let me take a look.

24:38.436 --> 24:39.896
- Oh, perfect.
- Mmm-hmm?

24:50.991 --> 24:52.409
What's that?

24:53.785 --> 24:56.997
"A strange creature has been
seen in the streets of Paris."

24:59.207 --> 25:01.835
"The beast is seven feet high,
is extremely hairy,

25:01.918 --> 25:04.379
"and has two big and red eyes.

25:04.462 --> 25:07.299
"Under those circumstances,
we recommend all citizens

25:07.382 --> 25:09.176
"not to go out alone at night."

25:09.259 --> 25:10.468
Ch, great!

25:11.344 --> 25:13.180
"Be cautious and do not panic."

25:15.098 --> 25:17.225
(SCREAMS)

25:18.435 --> 25:20.478
Raoul! You scared me!
What are you doing here?

25:20.729 --> 25:22.898
You scared me! And I'm working here!

25:22.981 --> 25:25.192
- Well, I hope nothing's broken.
- No, I'm fine.

25:25.275 --> 25:27.319
I'm talking about the champagne, you idiot!

25:28.111 --> 25:29.404
Look at me! I'm a mess!

25:29.487 --> 25:31.072
Here comes the drama queen.

25:31.156 --> 25:33.617
Come on. It's nothing. Here.

25:33.742 --> 25:35.577
Give me that! You're making it worse.

25:36.244 --> 25:38.622
Oh, great. Now, I have to change again!

25:38.788 --> 25:42.083
Uh, not a bad idea.
Brown is definitely not your colour.

25:43.001 --> 25:45.212
I see. You're a fashion expert now.

25:45.295 --> 25:46.922
Very credible with that straw coat on.

25:47.005 --> 25:49.591
- It's not straw.
- I see nothing has changed.

25:49.674 --> 25:52.010
Still the same birdbrain you were
in the first grade.

25:52.093 --> 25:53.803
And you're still so, so...

25:53.887 --> 25:54.888
$0 you!

25:54.971 --> 25:57.724
- What a repartee!
-(MIMICKING) What a repartee!

25:57.807 --> 26:00.685
Oh, I'm so smart. I use words like repartee.

26:00.769 --> 26:02.562
Look at me. Look at how amazing I am!

26:02.979 --> 26:05.523
(MIMICKING) Ooh, I'm so dumb.
Oh. I fell on my butt again!

26:05.607 --> 26:09.486
(MIMICKING) I'm a star. I'm a princess.
But I sing like a frog!

26:09.569 --> 26:11.571
- Oh. I get it.
- You get what?

26:11.655 --> 26:13.448
- You're jealous.
-(LAUGHS) Oh, yeah, I'm jealous.

26:13.531 --> 26:14.741
You're jealous of my success.

26:14.824 --> 26:16.618
- It makes you feel small.
-(LAUGHS)

26:17.202 --> 26:18.578
- Listen, honey...
- Don't you honey me.

26:18.662 --> 26:21.081
Listen honey. I'm doing just fine, okay?

26:21.164 --> 26:23.583
Women like me, men want to be me,

26:24.251 --> 26:28.004
uh, men want to be with the women
who like me.

26:28.171 --> 26:30.507
And the women, uh, want to be...

26:31.007 --> 26:33.426
The men who want to be with me...

26:35.053 --> 26:36.137
I'm popular and creative.

26:36.513 --> 26:37.555
Creative?

26:37.847 --> 26:39.349
You mean that piece of junk?

26:39.891 --> 26:42.852
Don't you... Don't you dare
bring Catherine into this!

26:43.186 --> 26:46.314
If you want to see popular and creative,
come see my show one night.

26:46.481 --> 26:49.526
Oh, wait! You can't. We don't accept losers.

26:49.693 --> 26:52.988
Oh, good one. Oh, pardon me,
your Royal Pain in the Buttness.

26:53.071 --> 26:54.906
I didn't realise you had to win
the Medal of Honour

26:54.990 --> 26:56.449
to gain entrance to the Cheese Hall!

26:56.533 --> 26:59.286
In your case, the only way you
will be admitted

26:59.369 --> 27:03.039
is if you show up with that medal
pinned to your chest.

27:03.164 --> 27:05.208
It would look great on your lovely straw coat!

27:05.292 --> 27:07.502
It's not... It's not... It's not straw!

27:08.420 --> 27:10.130
-(SNORTING)
-(LAUGHING)

27:10.213 --> 27:11.715
Ah, and one more thing.

27:11.798 --> 27:12.966
If you come with that medal,

27:13.049 --> 27:16.428
the best table will be waiting along with
all the champagne you can drink.

27:16.511 --> 27:17.595
On the house.

27:17.679 --> 27:18.722
(GRUNTING)

27:20.974 --> 27:22.017
(NEIGHING)

27:23.059 --> 27:25.520
LUCILLE: Albert! Can you come and get
the champagne inside?

27:25.937 --> 27:28.231
ALBERT: I'm in the bathroom!
LUCILLE: Now!

27:28.315 --> 27:29.607
- ALBERT: Okay, okay!
-(SIGHS)

27:29.983 --> 27:31.026
Pest!

27:32.193 --> 27:33.320
(GRUNTING)

27:33.403 --> 27:34.988
- There is a monster in Paris!
-(SCREAMS)

27:35.071 --> 27:36.906
People are scared!

27:37.657 --> 27:38.992
Give me one! Here.

27:39.200 --> 27:40.410
Thanks.

27:47.584 --> 27:48.626
Huh?

28:01.389 --> 28:02.724
How is it going up there?

28:03.016 --> 28:04.351
I'm close.

28:06.144 --> 28:08.188
POLICEMAN: Would you just check
over there...

28:08.396 --> 28:10.273
Let's see... Okay.

28:10.482 --> 28:11.524
There... Oh.

28:11.608 --> 28:13.610
POLICEMAN 3: Let's search thoroughly.
Look everywhere.

28:13.693 --> 28:14.694
(CHARLES SCREECHING)

28:15.111 --> 28:17.405
(SIGHS) Oh!

28:18.615 --> 28:21.743
Wait a minute. What is this?

28:42.055 --> 28:43.056
Oh, my God!

28:44.808 --> 28:46.476
Oh, this is a nightmare!

28:48.978 --> 28:51.564
Emile! It's a nightmare! I've lost all my clients.

28:51.898 --> 28:53.233
(EXCLAIMS)

28:54.818 --> 28:56.820
- What's that?
- It's the monster!

28:57.153 --> 28:58.655
The monster that we created!

28:59.114 --> 29:01.408
Yes, our own monster. He's got your eyes.

29:01.783 --> 29:02.784
And, Uh, my hairy legs!

29:02.867 --> 29:03.910
What are we going to do?

29:04.702 --> 29:07.414
Everything's fine. Nothing happened.
It's not our fault.

29:08.540 --> 29:09.624
(PANTING) Besides, nobody knows
we were there!

29:09.707 --> 29:12.001
Could have been anybody!
Could have been anybody.

29:12.085 --> 29:14.170
Sorry to interrupt the show, gentlemen,

29:14.254 --> 29:16.840
but I think you are about to
be the stars of the next feature.

29:17.132 --> 29:19.175
It's called The Interrogation!

29:19.843 --> 29:21.261
(WHIMPERING)

29:21.803 --> 29:23.012
(CLEARS THROAT)

29:23.096 --> 29:28.351
The way I see it, humanity is
divided in two different categories.

29:29.310 --> 29:32.730
The faceless and nameless masses

29:33.106 --> 29:36.401
living their lives like cockroaches,

29:37.152 --> 29:40.196
and those with a great destiny,

29:40.363 --> 29:42.657
those like you and me.

29:43.700 --> 29:47.203
You're very kind, Commissioner,
but I'm just a singer.

29:47.370 --> 29:48.371
Oh, don't be modest.

29:49.330 --> 29:52.375
You see, I'm due to inaugurate
the new railway.

29:53.209 --> 29:54.961
Everybody will talk about it

29:55.044 --> 29:58.423
and I would be honoured
to have you open the event

29:58.506 --> 30:01.134
and stand by my side.

30:01.217 --> 30:04.304
Because you're not just a singer,
you're a star.

30:04.888 --> 30:07.765
Shining brighter than all others,

30:07.849 --> 30:11.227
lighting the way to a brilliant future.

30:12.103 --> 30:15.565
For you, for me, for us.

30:16.191 --> 30:18.818
Uh, that's very nice of you,

30:19.235 --> 30:23.156
but don't you think it's
a little early to refer to us as "us"?

30:23.573 --> 30:25.742
(CLEARS THROAT) Excuse me?

30:26.451 --> 30:27.577
Yes, Paté?

30:27.660 --> 30:30.830
I don't mean to interrupt,
but I have extremely important news.

30:31.331 --> 30:33.041
- What?
- The monster...

30:33.500 --> 30:35.460
I have three suspects.

30:38.338 --> 30:39.422
(WHIMPERS)

30:41.216 --> 30:42.759
Now, if you'll look very closely

30:43.176 --> 30:45.178
right here, just before the explosion...

30:45.261 --> 30:46.554
See that little black dot?

30:46.638 --> 30:48.264
It's a flea from the monkey's fur.

30:48.681 --> 30:51.809
I believe that the combination
of these potions

30:52.769 --> 30:53.937
turned it into

30:59.734 --> 31:02.237
-the monster!
- Bravo, Paté!

31:02.570 --> 31:05.532
Bravo! A giant flea!

31:05.615 --> 31:08.284
This is exactly what I've been looking for!

31:08.576 --> 31:09.577
(LAUGHS)

31:10.036 --> 31:12.539
Excuse me, sir. I'm just starting out in life.

31:12.622 --> 31:13.706
I don't want to go to jail.

31:13.790 --> 31:16.376
Prison's a low-growth market
for home deliveries.

31:16.459 --> 31:18.086
Arrest the monkey! It was his flea!

31:19.337 --> 31:21.464
Prison? Who said anything about prison?

31:21.798 --> 31:23.424
This is a story about heroes.

31:23.800 --> 31:25.802
Heroes don't go to prison.

31:26.469 --> 31:28.721
- But, sir, they're guilty!
- Guilty of what?

31:28.805 --> 31:32.892
